[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Train a Model per Segment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Each segment gets a model tuned to its demand pattern. The demo implements three model families:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Smooth segment:** a simple seasonal-naive plus level-trend baseline that captures weekly seasonality and a multi-day moving level. Production swaps this for Prophet, ETS (exponential smoothing), or a SARIMA model.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Intermittent / Lumpy / Erratic segments:** the Syntetos-Boylan Approximation (SBA), a less-biased variant of Croston's method that decomposes demand into (size-when-non-zero, inter-arrival-time) and forecasts each piece separately.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Procedure-driven segment:** a two-stage model that forecasts the case-volume series with the smooth-segment baseline and multiplies by a per-case usage rate computed from the SKU master.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m In production this step is one or several SageMaker training jobs running in parallel via the Step Functions Map state, with each job producing a versioned model artifact written to the model-artifact S3 bucket. The demo collapses the training into pure-Python helpers so you can read the math.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m class SmoothModel:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Weekly-seasonal baseline plus level + linear trend.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Production replaces this with Prophet, ETS, or SARIMA. The
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     interface (fit, predict_horizon, sigma) is what matters: any
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     model that can produce point forecasts and a residual standard
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     deviation drops in.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def __init__(self):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.dow_factor      = {}     # day-of-week -> seasonal factor
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.level           = 0.0    # final level
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.trend_per_day   = 0.0    # estimated daily trend
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.sigma           = 0.0    # residual standard deviation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def fit(self, daily_quantities, dates):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # 3a. Estimate level + trend by ordinary least squares on the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # de-seasonalized series. Compute weekly seasonality first
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # by averaging quantity within each day-of-week.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         n = len(daily_quantities)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if n == 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return self
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         dow_buckets = defaultdict(list)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for q, d_iso in zip(daily_quantities, dates):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dow = date.fromisoformat(d_iso).weekday()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dow_buckets[dow].append(q)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         overall_mean = mean(daily_quantities) if daily_quantities else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.dow_factor = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dow: (mean(qs) / overall_mean) if overall_mean > 0 else 1.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for dow, qs in dow_buckets.items()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # 3b. Linear trend on the de-seasonalized series.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         deseasonalized = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             q / self.dow_factor.get(date.fromisoformat(d).weekday(), 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for q, d in zip(daily_quantities, dates)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if n >= 2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             xs   = list(range(n))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             x_m  = sum(xs) / n
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             y_m  = sum(deseasonalized) / n
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             num  = sum((xs[i] - x_m) * (deseasonalized[i] - y_m) for i in range(n))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             den  = sum((xs[i] - x_m) ** 2 for i in range(n))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.trend_per_day = num / den if den > 0 else 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.level         = y_m + self.trend_per_day * (n - 1 - x_m)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.trend_per_day = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.level         = deseasonalized[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # 3c. Residuals against the in-sample fit produce the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # forecast-error standard deviation we feed into the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # safety-stock calculation. A real production model uses
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # rolling-origin cross-validation on the validation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # window, not in-sample residuals.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         residuals = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for i, (q, d) in enumerate(zip(daily_quantities, dates)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             f = self._fitted_value(i, d, n)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             residuals.append(q - f)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if len(residuals) > 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.sigma = stdev(residuals)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.sigma = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return self
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def _fitted_value(self, t, d_iso, n):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Reconstruct the in-sample fitted value for residuals.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         anchor = self.level - self.trend_per_day * (n - 1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ds_val = anchor + self.trend_per_day * t
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         dow    = date.fromisoformat(d_iso).weekday()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return ds_val * self.dow_factor.get(dow, 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def predict_horizon(self, last_date_iso, horizon_days):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         last_d   = date.fromisoformat(last_date_iso)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         forecasts = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for h in range(1, horizon_days + 1):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             future_d = last_d + timedelta(days=h)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ds_val   = self.level + self.trend_per_day * h
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dow_f    = self.dow_factor.get(future_d.weekday(), 1.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             point    = max(0.0, ds_val * dow_f)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             forecasts.append({"date": future_d.isoformat(), "point": point})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return forecasts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m class SBAModel:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Syntetos-Boylan Approximation for intermittent demand.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Croston decomposes intermittent demand into a non-zero
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     demand size series and an inter-arrival time series, then
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     forecasts each with simple exponential smoothing. Croston's
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     original estimator is biased upward; SBA applies a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     correction factor of (1 - alpha/2) to remove it. The
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     forecast for any future day is constant: size / interval *
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (1 - alpha/2).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def __init__(self, alpha=0.1):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.alpha           = alpha
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.size_smoothed   = 0.0  # exp-smoothed non-zero size
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.interval_smoothed = 0.0  # exp-smoothed inter-arrival time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.daily_forecast  = 0.0  # point forecast per day
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.sigma           = 0.0  # residual std dev
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def fit(self, daily_quantities, dates):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if not daily_quantities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return self
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Walk through the series tracking days since last non-zero
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # demand. Apply exponential smoothing to the size series
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # and the inter-arrival series, but only update at the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # non-zero points (this is what makes it Croston-style).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         size_s     = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         interval_s = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         gap_count  = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for q in daily_quantities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             gap_count += 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if q > 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if size_s is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     size_s     = float(q)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     interval_s = float(gap_count)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     size_s     = self.alpha * float(q)        + (1 - self.alpha) * size_s
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     interval_s = self.alpha * float(gap_count) + (1 - self.alpha) * interval_s
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 gap_count = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if size_s is None or interval_s is None or interval_s == 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.daily_forecast = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             self.sigma          = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return self
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    799[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.size_smoothed     = size_s
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    800[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.interval_smoothed = interval_s
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    801[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    802[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # SBA bias correction: multiply by (1 - alpha/2) to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    803[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # remove Croston's upward bias. Without this, intermittent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    804[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # SKUs systematically over-stock.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    805[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         self.daily_forecast = (size_s / interval_s) * (1 - self.alpha / 2.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    806[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Residual standard deviation against the constant
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # forecast. SBA forecasts are constant per day, which
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # makes residual variance simple to compute. Production
